div1.p:
The following material has been found among the records of

The Adjutant General's Office and the Office of the Secretary of War:



On yellow fever: outbreak of epidemics and precautionary

measures to be taken; methods for treating yellow fever;

data furnished by The Surgeon General in regard to its

prevalence in Cuba; its existence among the Army of Cuban

Pacification;

on Columbia Barracks: reports of surgeons; operations of

post exchange; outbreak of yellow fever; post inspection

report; concerning clothing supplies;

on Camp Columbia: reports of chaplain; post inspection

report; reports of surgeons; births and deaths; repairs

to buildings;

on Dr. Jesse W. Lazear: assignment to duty on infectious

diseases board, 1900; report of his death; inventory of

his personal effects; concerning removal of his remains;

on Dr. James Carroll: his movements and assignments from

1891 to 1909; attendance at medical society meetings;

report of his death.
